                <p>
                    <app loc="1"><lem resp="#cdlBE">Ἀπόλλων<supplied reason="lost">ος</supplied></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#mohamed2003">Ἀπόλλων<supplied reason="lost">ι</supplied></rdg>
                    </app>
               </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Autel</supplied> d'Apollon.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Altar</supplied> of Apollo.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Altare</supplied> di Apollo.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The names of gods on such altars are rather owner's marks than dedications, hence the restored genitive case rather than the dative of the first editor.</p>
